HEADWORD: Lieberkühn
<hw>Lie"ber*k⟦uum⟧hn</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧"b⟦etil⟧r*k⟦usdot⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Named after a German physician and instrument
maker, <person>J. N. <etsep>Lieberk⟦uum⟧hn</etsep></person>.]</ety>
<fld>(Optics)</fld> <def>A concave metallic mirror attached to the
object-glass end of a microscope, to throw down light on opaque objects;
a reflector.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

